{
  "texts": [
    "We have observed a different process of creating the plot and characters in a detective story (Table 1, Story 5).",
    "From the perspective of logic, it is better to develop the action from the end, starting from the murderthe novel's main mystery.",
    "It helps to get a comprehensive concept, understand the story's key message, and give chatbot more details that could be used in further answers.",
    "For example, we asked the chatbot who truly killed Professor Haynes, then developed the portrait of the antagonist, then generated three potential suspect characters, and only after fully understanding the picture of the murder did we start to ask the chatbot about the portrait of Detective Sarah Michaels.",
    "This leads us to the thought that while developing the plot, the human author creates characters, inquires about their psychological portraits, and finds out their motives for acting."
  ]
}